Metadata

# Metadata
metadata <- read.delim("/work/proteomics/02_data/Metadata_Cohort_100723.csv", sep = ";", dec = ",", header = T) %>% 
  mutate(intern = gsub("K", "", .$K.no.),
         Diagnosis = gsub("Unknown", "MSA", .$Diagnosis)) # 1418 should be MSA

sample.meta <- read.delim("/work/proteomics/02_data/Kohorte_info.csv", sep = ";", header = T, dec = ",")

# Remove PFC samples
smeta <- sample.meta %>% 
  filter(!grepl("PFC", Compartment)) %>% 
  mutate(area = grepl.replace(Compartment, c("Substantia nigra", "Frontal cortex", "Cerebral cortex", "Putamen", "Medulla", "Cerebellum", "Striatum"), c("SN", "FC", "CER", "STR", "MED", "CER", "STR")),
         k = gsub("K", "", Intern) %>% 
           strsplit("-") %>% 
           sget(1)) %>% 
  mutate(comb = paste(k, area, sep = "-"))

Region-based, no groups, with NA, with imputation

# Isolate RR samples
rr.vec <- df.clean.raw %>% 
  pull(label) %>%
  strsplit("BREG.", fixed = T) %>% 
  sget(2) %>% 
  strsplit(".", fixed = T) %>% 
  sget(1) %>% 
  .[grepl("RR", .)] %>% 
  gsub("RR1", "RR-1", .) %>% 
  gsub("RR2", "RR-2", .)

smeta.rr <- smeta %>% 
  filter(Sample %in% rr.vec)

# Other samples
df.other <- df.clean.raw %>% 
  filter(!comb %in% smeta.rr$comb)

smeta.other <- smeta %$% 
  .[match(unique(comb), comb), ] %>% 
  filter(comb %in% df.clean.raw$comb,
         comb %in% df.other$comb) %>% 
  dplyr::select(-area, -k, -comb)

# Make new sample-wise metadata
smeta.new <- smeta.rr %>% 
  dplyr::select(-area, -k, -comb) %>% 
  rbind(smeta.other) %>% 
  mutate(k = gsub("K", "", Intern) %>% 
           strsplit("-") %>% sget(1)) %>% 
  mutate(Age = metadata$Age[match(k, metadata$intern)],
         Sex = metadata$Sex[match(k, metadata$intern)],
         PMI = metadata$PMI[match(k, metadata$intern)],
         Subtype = metadata$Subtype[match(k, metadata$intern)],
         Duration  = metadata$Duration[match(k, metadata$intern)],
         Hemisphere = metadata$Hemisphere[match(k, metadata$intern)])

rm(smeta.rr, smeta.other, df.other, smeta)

spl.idx <- df.clean.raw %>% 
  pull(condition)

spl.list <- df.clean.raw %>% 
  pull(id) %>% 
  split(spl.idx)

list.assay <- spl.list %>% 
  lapply(\(cc) dat.assay[, cc]) %>% 
  # lapply(\(cc) `colnames<-`(cc, df.clean$intern[match(colnames(cc), df.clean$sample_id)])) %>% 
  lapply(\(cc) `colnames<-`(cc, df.clean.raw$intern[match(colnames(cc), df.clean.raw$id)]))# %>% 
  # lapply(\(cc) cc[, colnames(.[[1]])]) %>% # Ensure same column order
    
all.samples <- list.assay %>% 
  lapply(colnames) %>% 
  unlist() %>% 
  unique()
  
list.assay %<>%
  names() %>% 
  lapply(\(cc) {
    mat <- list.assay[[cc]]
    missing_samples <- setdiff(df.clean.raw$intern, colnames(mat))
    
    # Add missing columns with NA
    for (sample in missing_samples) {
      mat <- cbind(mat, setNames(as.data.frame(matrix(NA, nrow = nrow(mat), ncol = 1)), sample))
    }
    
    # Reorder columns to match the first matrix's column order
    mat <- mat[, unique(df.clean.raw$intern), drop = FALSE]
    mat %<>% as.matrix()
  }) %>% 
  lapply(\(cc) cc[matrixStats::rowVars(cc, na.rm = T) > 1, ]) %>% # Filter low variance proteins
  setNames(names(list.assay))

# Check that the same column names are in all matrices of list.assay
all(sapply(list.assay, function(x) all(colnames(x) %in% colnames(list.assay[[1]]))))

#                      area != "FC")

spl.idx <- df.clean %>% 
  filter(comb %in% df.clean.raw$comb.raw) %>% 
  pull(condition)

spl.list <- df.clean %>% 
  filter(comb %in% df.clean.raw$comb.raw) %>% 
  pull(id) %>% 
  split(spl.idx)

list.assay <- spl.list %>% 
  lapply(\(cc) dat.assay.noimp[, cc]) %>%
  lapply(\(cc) `colnames<-`(cc, df.clean.raw$intern[match(colnames(cc), df.clean.raw$id)])) %>% 
  setNames(names(spl.list))
    
all.samples <- list.assay %>% 
  lapply(colnames) %>% 
  unlist() %>% 
  unique()
  
list.assay %<>%
  names() %>% 
  lapply(\(cc) {
    mat <- list.assay[[cc]]
    missing_samples <- setdiff(df.clean.raw$intern, colnames(mat))
    
    # Add missing columns with NA
    for (sample in missing_samples) {
      mat <- cbind(mat, setNames(as.data.frame(matrix(NA, nrow = nrow(mat), ncol = 1)), sample))
    }
    
    # Reorder columns to match the first matrix's column order
    mat <- mat[, unique(df.clean.raw$intern), drop = FALSE]
    mat %<>% 
      as.matrix() %>% 
      `rownames<-`(paste(rownames(.), cc, sep = "_"))
    
    # Filter low variance proteins
    rv <- matrixStats::rowVars(mat, na.rm = T) %>% 
      .[!is.na(.)] %>% 
      .[. > 0.5]
    
    mat %<>% .[rownames(.) %in% names(rv), ]
    
    return(mat)
  }) %>%
  setNames(names(list.assay))

# Check that the same column names are in all matrices of list.assay
all(sapply(list.assay, function(x) all(colnames(x) %in% colnames(list.assay[[1]]))))

Overlap between models with/without imputation

Load data

library(UpSetR)

areas <- c("CER", "FC", "MED", "SN" ,"STR")

imp <- areas %>% 
  lapply(\(x) h5read("/work/proteomics/02_data/mofa_nogroups_withna_withimp.hdf5", name = paste0("/features/", x))) %>% 
  lapply(strsplit, "_") %>% 
  lapply(sget, 1) %>% 
  setNames(areas)

noimp <- areas %>% 
  lapply(\(x) h5read("/work/proteomics/02_data/mofa_nogroups_withna_noimp.hdf5", name = paste0("/features/", x))) %>% 
  lapply(strsplit, "_") %>% 
  lapply(sget, 1) %>% 
  setNames(areas)

se.imp <- qread("/work/proteomics/02_data/03_objects/preprocessed_data.qs")$dat.clean

imp.logi <- se.imp@elementMetadata@listData %>% 
  .[grepl("imputed", names(.))] %>% 
  setNames(areas)

Within datasets

imp %>% 
  fromList() %>% 
  upset(title = "Within dataset, with imputation")

noimp %>% 
  fromList() %>% 
  upset(title = "Within dataset, without imputation")

Between datasets

areas %>% 
  lapply(\(aa) {
    WithImputation = imp[[aa]]
    
    Imputed = imp.logi[[aa]] %>% 
      .[.] %>%
      .[names(.) %in% WithImputation] %>% 
      names()
    
    NoImputation = noimp[[aa]]
    
    list(WithImputation = WithImputation, 
         Imputed = Imputed,
         NoImputation = NoImputation) %>% 
      fromList() %>% 
      upset(nsets = 3, title = aa)
  })
